00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:13,780
♫ I promise I will always be true and honest to you ♫

38
00:03:25,420 --> 00:03:30,410
[Love By Chance 2: A Chance to Love]

39
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:36,120
[6 months later]

40
00:03:42,830 --> 00:03:45,300
Dude, wake up! I'm gonna...

41
00:03:52,060 --> 00:03:54,590
Geez... Why are you so handsome?

42
00:03:54,590 --> 00:03:56,490
I've slept with you many times.

43
00:03:56,490 --> 00:03:58,530
Why have I never noticed?

44
00:04:01,100 --> 00:04:04,880
You just realized? That you've got an amazing boyfriend.

45
00:04:06,060 --> 00:04:08,850
You're really not that confident in yourself, are you?
(T/N: He's being sarcastic)

46
00:04:10,910 --> 00:04:12,940
It's true, isn't it?

47
00:04:12,940 --> 00:04:14,180
Yeah, I won't argue with you.

48
00:04:14,180 --> 00:04:16,710
You should get up now. I have to go to university early, too.

49
00:04:16,710 --> 00:04:19,290
There's an orientation for the soccer team newbies today. I'm already late.

50
00:04:19,290 --> 00:04:22,940
I was going to go home yesterday, but you kept whining for me to stay over at the condo.

51
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:27,590
Me?

52
00:04:27,590 --> 00:04:29,680
I was the one whining?

53
00:04:31,550 --> 00:04:33,720
Well, I wanted to stay, too.

54
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:35,470
Just hurry up!

55
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:38,070
I'm up.

56
00:04:38,070 --> 00:04:39,580
Wait just a second.

57
00:04:39,580 --> 00:04:42,710
Hurry up, okay? I'll make some toast while I wait.

58
00:04:42,710 --> 00:04:44,420
Hurry, get up!

59
00:04:45,770 --> 00:04:47,600
Get up now!

60
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:10,410
Thanks for sending me off. I'm off!

61
00:05:10,410 --> 00:05:12,010
Cantaloupe.

62
00:05:13,780 --> 00:05:16,810
Dude... You're always calling me by my full name.

63
00:05:16,810 --> 00:05:18,460
I not embarrassed by you.

64
00:05:18,460 --> 00:05:21,460
Every time we do it, you're always calling me by my full name anyway.

65
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:25,990
Do you remember what day it is next week?

66
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:31,450
Next week…? It's Tuesday!

67
00:05:31,450 --> 00:05:34,530
Well, today is Tuesday, so next week it'll also be Tuesday!

68
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:40,050
You really can't remember?

69
00:05:41,670 --> 00:05:44,860
So... why do I have to remember that?

70
00:05:48,490 --> 00:05:51,820
Aren't you already late? You should quickly get going.

71
00:05:51,820 --> 00:05:54,220
Okay. Then I'll get going.

72
00:06:01,420 --> 00:06:03,650
Did I do something wrong?

73
00:06:04,860 --> 00:06:06,100
Maybe not?

74
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,750
Whatever.

75
00:06:15,790 --> 00:06:20,280
No! I won't talk to you! I want to talk to Dad!

76
00:06:21,340 --> 00:06:24,340
But today Khun Tul might come home late.

77
00:06:24,940 --> 00:06:27,220
Khun Phu, can you tell me instead?

78
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:30,250
If I can't talk to Dad, then I'll talk to Uncle Tin!

79
00:06:30,250 --> 00:06:32,500
I'll talk to P'Can!

80
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:36,940
Then next time, I'll tell Khun Can for you.

81
00:06:36,940 --> 00:06:41,080
But today... if you need anything, Khun Phu, can you tell me?

82
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:44,090
No! I don't want to talk to you!
(T/N: The form of 'you' Phu is using is considered disrespectful for someone younger to use towards an elder)

83
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:45,960
Why not?

84
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:48,450
Because I don't like you.

85
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:51,720
Why don't you like me, Khun Phu?

86
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:55,320
Don't know. Don't want to think about it. Don't care.

87
00:06:57,650 --> 00:06:59,440
Khu Phu.

88
00:07:00,300 --> 00:07:04,060
Stop nagging me! I already said that I don't want to talk to you!

89
00:07:04,060 --> 00:07:07,680
Nong Phu! You're speaking very rudely.

90
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:11,420
Yay! Dad is back!

91
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:21,110
Dad is back.

92
00:07:21,110 --> 00:07:23,820
But someone said that you were misbehaving.

93
00:07:25,210 --> 00:07:27,720
I wasn't misbehaving...

94
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,950
Then, why didn't you call Hin "Uncle Hin"?

95
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:31,700
How could you call him "you"?

96
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:36,630
But Grandma said I could call people in this house whatever I wanted though.

97
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:41,140
But I've never taught you to speak impolitely with your elders.

98
00:07:41,140 --> 00:07:44,660
Nong Phu, you even call Grandma Glin as "Grandma Glin."

99
00:07:44,660 --> 00:07:46,640
Hmm, again.

100
00:07:47,290 --> 00:07:48,550
What again?

101
00:07:48,550 --> 00:07:50,660
Dad, you're siding with Uncle Hin again.

102
00:07:50,660 --> 00:07:52,420
Dad, you don't love me anymore.

103
00:07:52,420 --> 00:07:56,610
I don't like Uncle Hin, because you love Uncle Hin.

104
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:03,120
Dad, you have to love me, all right?

105
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:06,210
Please don't love Uncle Hin.

106
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,520
Khun Phu.

107
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:14,790
Your dad loves you a lot.

108
00:08:14,790 --> 00:08:16,680
He loves you more than anyone else.

109
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:18,990
He loves you the most in the whole world.

110
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:22,490
And not only your dad, Khun Phu.

111
00:08:22,490 --> 00:08:25,380
Everyone in this house loves you alot, Khun Phu.

112
00:08:25,380 --> 00:08:27,420
You too, Uncle Hin?

113
00:08:27,420 --> 00:08:30,510
That's right. I also love you a lot, Khun Phu.

114
00:08:33,380 --> 00:08:36,390
Dad, I'm sleepy now.

115
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:38,710
You stubborn child.

116
00:08:38,710 --> 00:08:41,210
I'm going to take my son up to sleep, all right?

117
00:08:41,210 --> 00:08:44,205
Come. Let's get you to bed.

118
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:25,040
Is Khun Phu already asleep?

119
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:31,420
Hey. I told you so many times already, didn't I? It's enough to just call him "Nong Phu,"

120
00:09:33,530 --> 00:09:35,910
But Khun Phu doesn't like me.

121
00:09:36,710 --> 00:09:40,340
Nong Phu doesn't like anyone who's close to his mom or dad.

122
00:09:40,340 --> 00:09:41,930
But I believe that one day

123
00:09:41,930 --> 00:09:46,350
he'll realize that this person, is the most important person in his dad's life.

124
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:51,450
The more you say such things,

125
00:09:51,450 --> 00:09:53,710
Khun Phupha will feel more unhappy.

126
00:09:54,810 --> 00:09:56,500
How many years did it take

127
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:59,240
before I was able to admit that I love you?

128
00:10:02,090 --> 00:10:03,890
20 years.

129
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:09,380
Although my son and I don't easily accept other people's love,

130
00:10:09,380 --> 00:10:12,994
but if we love them, we'll give them all of our heart.

131
00:10:24,330 --> 00:10:26,160
Wait.

132
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:29,220
Khun Tul, you have some documents you need to read through before you go into tomorrow's meeting.

133
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:31,940
It's way past office hours, Mr. Secretary.

134
00:10:31,940 --> 00:10:35,120
This time needs to be used for other things.

135
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,010
But the documents...

136
00:10:40,010 --> 00:10:41,790
Geez! Khun Tul!

137
00:10:49,610 --> 00:10:52,070
Here, here. You have to hold it like this. Like C.

138
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:54,350
- Right here?
- That's right.

139
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:58,220
Okay, like that.

140
00:10:58,220 --> 00:11:00,820
Another one. Bring it down. Yeah.

141
00:11:01,450 --> 00:11:02,980
Got it?

142
00:11:04,010 --> 00:11:05,650
What are you guys doing?

143
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:10,220
You guys are sitting that close?

144
00:11:10,220 --> 00:11:12,260
How's this close?

145
00:11:20,570 --> 00:11:22,600
- Then I'm going to head off first.
- Huh?

146
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,210
- Leaving already?
- Yeah.

147
00:11:24,210 --> 00:11:26,700
I happen to have soccer practice with some friends.

148
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:29,130
Oh! Okay, okay.

149
00:11:29,130 --> 00:11:31,980
- Then I'll see you later.
- Yeah okay.

150
00:11:36,990 --> 00:11:39,450
- Bye.
- See ya.

151
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:44,200
Was he here a long time?

152
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,880
Yeah, he came...

153
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:47,190
for just about an hour.

154
00:11:47,190 --> 00:11:50,240
Are... you all right, dude? Why do you look so irritated?

155
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:52,620
Is it about Tar?

156
00:11:52,620 --> 00:11:54,060
No.

157
00:11:54,810 --> 00:11:56,540
It doesn't have anything to do with Tar.

158
00:11:56,540 --> 00:11:57,940
What?

159
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:00,810
It's about you though.

160
00:12:00,810 --> 00:12:03,720
What? Me?

161
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:08,120
It's nothing, forget it.

162
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:10,570
Tell me!

163
00:12:10,570 --> 00:12:13,850
Tell me. Please?

164
00:12:13,850 --> 00:12:15,440
What's wrong?

165
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,110
It's nothing.

166
00:12:18,890 --> 00:12:20,630
Forget about it.

167
00:12:20,630 --> 00:12:22,660
Okay, okay.

168
00:12:28,220 --> 00:12:32,500
Next week… What day is it?

169
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:36,361
The day mom makes Chicken Rice?

170
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:40,930
But Ai'Tin doesn't like Chicken Rice…

171
00:12:44,143 --> 00:12:47,980
Ahhh! My head hurts! I can't figure it out.

172
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:51,740
What day is it?

173
00:12:52,360 --> 00:12:53,822
Ai'Can.

174
00:12:55,950 --> 00:12:57,820
Ai'Can!

175
00:12:57,820 --> 00:13:00,540
P'No! What's with you?!

176
00:13:00,590 --> 00:13:03,240
If I had a heart attack, would you be able to take responsibility?

177
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:06,625
Wouldn't that be great? Then our world would have one less crazy person.

178
00:13:06,625 --> 00:13:11,480
Crazy… Stupid… Let me seriously ask you... Do you even love me at all?

179
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:13,660
Do I have to love you?

180
00:13:13,660 --> 00:13:16,890
Whatever. I don't want to repeat and play along with this nonsense anymore.

181
00:13:16,890 --> 00:13:19,091
But what about you, P'No. You graduated ages ago.

182
00:13:19,091 --> 00:13:21,300
What are you doing here?

183
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:24,718
Let me seriously ask you... Do you not have any work to do?

184
00:13:24,718 --> 00:13:26,250
Ouch!

185
00:13:26,250 --> 00:13:28,140
Of course, I have work.

186
00:13:28,140 --> 00:13:31,100
But I just stopped by to see the coach is all.

187
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:32,460
I just happened to see you.

188
00:13:32,460 --> 00:13:34,320
So what's wrong?

189
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:37,530
Well, it's Ai'Tin…

190
00:13:37,530 --> 00:13:40,140
He's mad at me for something, and I don't even know why.

191
00:13:43,690 --> 00:13:45,700
You're asking me, but would I even know?

192
00:13:47,450 --> 00:13:48,860
I knew it.

193
00:13:48,860 --> 00:13:51,130
Asking you is such a waste of time.

194
00:13:51,130 --> 00:13:53,360
Even asking Ai'Ae would be more helpful.

195
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:57,370
Such a waste of time.

196
00:13:57,370 --> 00:13:58,740
Hey, Ai'Can!

197
00:13:58,740 --> 00:14:00,490
Hey! Come back here first!

198
00:14:00,490 --> 00:14:02,070
Do you not see me as your older bro?

199
00:14:02,070 --> 00:14:04,000
Ai'Can!

200
00:14:04,590 --> 00:14:07,880
Who the hell is texting me on Line? I'm annoyed as it is.

201
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,880
P'No!

202
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:33,670
Have you finished talking to the coach already?

203
00:14:33,670 --> 00:14:35,450
Yeah, I'm done talking already.

204
00:14:35,450 --> 00:14:38,570
But really, you didn't have to come and pick me up.

205
00:14:38,570 --> 00:14:41,130
P'No. I really wanted to come and pick you up though.

206
00:14:41,140 --> 00:14:43,300
Please let me pick you up.

207
00:14:45,950 --> 00:14:48,009
Okay, fine.

208
00:14:48,009 --> 00:14:50,230
You can pick me up.

209
00:14:50,230 --> 00:14:51,799
Really?

210
00:14:51,799 --> 00:14:53,480
That's too close, Ai'Kla. Too close...

211
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:55,451
Step back a bit.

212
00:15:00,670 --> 00:15:03,180
It's because I'm letting you make up for your mistakes.

213
00:15:03,180 --> 00:15:05,470
But you have to promise that from now on that

214
00:15:05,470 --> 00:15:07,530
you won't lie to me again.

215
00:15:08,090 --> 00:15:11,320
I promise, P'No! I promise!

216
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:14,020
Hand... Your hand, Ai'Kla. Your hand...

217
00:15:17,710 --> 00:15:21,380
Well... you're so cute though...

218
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:25,960
I'm not talking to you anymore.

219
00:15:29,980 --> 00:15:31,080
Hey.

220
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:32,965
Didn't you say you were going to send me off?

221
00:15:32,965 --> 00:15:34,654
Hurry up then!

222
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:40,400
I'm coming right now!

223
00:16:05,310 --> 00:16:08,122
Khun Phu, would you like to eat some ice cream?

224
00:16:08,122 --> 00:16:10,495
I don't want any. I don't want to eat it.

225
00:16:13,850 --> 00:16:16,140
You still can't get Phupa to warm up to you yet?

226
00:16:16,140 --> 00:16:18,530
Uncle Tin!

227
00:16:27,589 --> 00:16:32,220
Even though you came back and immediately received the position of being my older brother's secretary.

228
00:16:32,220 --> 00:16:34,590
You completed every project.

229
00:16:35,370 --> 00:16:38,260
But with such a small child like this,

230
00:16:38,260 --> 00:16:40,799
you still can't win him over?

231
00:16:42,940 --> 00:16:46,360
And what about you? What's the matter?

232
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:49,140
I'm mad at Dad.

233
00:16:49,140 --> 00:16:50,880
Why?

234
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:53,980
Dad doesn't listen to anything I say.

235
00:16:56,270 --> 00:16:58,050
Then...

236
00:16:58,670 --> 00:16:59,840
Can you tell Uncle Tin?

237
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:03,710
I want to go to the beach!

238
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:06,490
You want to go with your dad, just the two of you?

239
00:17:06,490 --> 00:17:08,940
I want to go with dad, go with Uncle Tin, and go with P'Can!

240
00:17:08,940 --> 00:17:11,440
Go with everyone!

241
00:17:14,430 --> 00:17:16,130
What about Uncle Hin then?

242
00:17:19,260 --> 00:17:21,520
Fine, Uncle Hin can come, too.

243
00:17:23,550 --> 00:17:25,010
Really?

244
00:17:26,070 --> 00:17:27,100
Who's talking to you, Uncle Hin?

245
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:29,430
I'm going to go eat some ice cream!

246
00:17:41,630 --> 00:17:43,545
He's just a kid being haughty.

247
00:17:44,940 --> 00:17:48,378
Isn't it because all the men in the Methanan family are like that?

248
00:17:56,090 --> 00:17:58,680
My mom wanted me to ask you...

249
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:00,570
for your birthday next week,

250
00:18:00,570 --> 00:18:03,182
would you like to eat anything special, Khun Tin?

251
00:18:08,190 --> 00:18:11,110
I probably want to devour the guy who forgot my birthday.

252
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:15,193
Forget it.

253
00:18:16,220 --> 00:18:20,080
I'm going to go take a shower. I have to go talk to my dad, too.

254
00:18:30,140 --> 00:18:32,600
He's definitely a man of the Methanan family.

255
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:36,910
You forgot P'Tin's birthday?

256
00:18:36,910 --> 00:18:38,310
Ai' Brother Can!

257
00:18:38,310 --> 00:18:40,350
